  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I looked into the existing components and I found that [PriceRanges](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/priceRanges.html) is pretty much the same as the [RangeInput](https://community.algolia.com/react-instantsearch/widgets/RangeInput.html). Basically the `PriceRanges` is a composition of a `RangeInput` with a list of ranges.\r\n\r\nSo instead of using the `connectRangeSlider` as connector, we might use the `connectPriceRanges` to implement the `RangeInput` widget and reuse the `RangeInput` component inside `PriceRanges`. With this we can remove the logic for the inputs in `PriceRanges` and handle only the refinement on ranges.\r\n\r\nAs a side note, we can also rename the `PriceRanges` widget (& connector) for a more generic name like `RangeInputList` (any ideas?) because it's not strictly limited to a range of prices. We can imagine it with sizes, weights...\r\n\r\nWhat do you think about it?\r\n",
